# Markdown / Documentation Standards

## Patterns to Always Use
- One H1 per file (`# Title`); use `##` / `###` for sections.
- Fenced code blocks with language tags where applicable.
- Relative links to repo files; full URLs for external references.
- Append-only policy for `SESSION_LOG.md` (never rewrite past entries).
- Keep line length readable (~100–120 chars soft wrap in prose).

## Patterns to Never Use
- Committing secrets, tokens, or personal paths that are not portable.
- Deleting or rewriting historical session log entries.
- Using HTML entities in fenced code or inline code (use literal characters).

## File Naming Convention
- `SCREAMING_SNAKE` or `PascalCase` for top-level guide filenames as established (`AGENTS.md`, `DIRECTIVES.md`); kebab-case acceptable for optional docs under `docs/`.

## Testing Requirement
- Documentation changes: human review; link check when adding many URLs.

## Context7 Library IDs (add "use context7" when using these)
- Cursor / Taskmaster CLI docs as needed via context7 when writing automation that depends on their APIs.
